
[1]android

   AN'DROID, n. [Gr. man and form.]

   A machine, in the human form, which, by certain springs, performs some
   of the natural motions of a living man. One of these machines, invented
   by M. Vaucanson, appeared at Paris is 1738, representing a flute
   player.
